                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390513-name-181" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-181" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-181" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390513-name-181" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM SMITH</persName>
                  </hi>. About eleven o'clock on the 9th of May I was in Thames-street, near Billingsgate, I felt a pull at my pocket—I turned, and saw the prisoner going off—I took him, and found my handkerchief in a long pocket in his trowsers—he said first that I did not take it from him, and then he said he had found it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I picked it up on the pavement, against a herring shop. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> It is quite impossible that I could have dropped it, not a second elapsed before I took him.</p>
